# Environment Variables for CEX Arbitrage Engine
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual API credentials

# MEXC Exchange API Credentials
# Leave empty for public-only access (no trading, just market data)
MEXC_API_KEY=
MEXC_SECRET_KEY=

# Gate.io Exchange API Credentials  
# Leave empty for public-only access (no trading, just market data)
GATEIO_API_KEY=
GATEIO_SECRET_KEY=

# Usage Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to create your local .env: 
#    cp .env.example .env
# 2. Edit .env and add your actual API credentials
# 3. The credentials will be automatically loaded when you run the application
# 4. Never commit the .env file to version control

# Security Notes:
# - API keys should be at least 10 characters long
# - Secret keys should be at least 20 characters long  
# - Add .env to your .gitignore file (should already be there)
# - Use read-only API keys when possible for testing
# - The system works in public mode without credentials (market data only)